<subSubSection pageId="142" pageNumber="143" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="142" pageNumber="143">
The very short pubescent sepals are a good character as are the very slender peduncles arising at or near 90°. There seems to be some variation in inflorescence branching, sometimes clearly dichasial (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Grey-Wilson &amp; Hewer</emphasis>
127), sometimes almost racemose (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Léonard">Leonard</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
5921).
</paragraph>
